{
  "date": "2026-03-26",
  "type": "daily",
  "executive_summary": "Today's valve updates reveal important clinical insights across all transcatheter platforms. New data shows tricuspid regurgitation proportionality affects T-TEER outcomes, while rapid atrial pacing proves unreliable for predicting pacemaker needs after TAVR. Several studies highlight serious complications with transcatheter tricuspid interventions, including bleeding, hemodynamic instability, and device failures\u2014findings that underscore the need for careful patient selection as these technologies mature. For clinicians managing structural heart disease patients, today's findings emphasize a recurring theme: transcatheter technologies continue to evolve rapidly, but with each advance comes new complications and selection challenges that require careful consideration. The tricuspid space, in particular, shows both promise and concerning signals about patient outcomes and procedural risks.",
